The paper discusses a new method for clustering data represented as tensors, which is a topic in machine learning and data analysis. Specifically, the paper focuses on spectral co-clustering, which is a technique for clustering multiple modes of a tensor simultaneously. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses applications of the method to text data, network data, and synthetic data, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
